Enums.Name: AnalyzeTextOutputType

AllowedValues.Name: FourSeverityLevels
AllowedValues.Description: Output severities in four levels, the value could be 0,2,4,6.

AllowedValues.Name: EightSeverityLevels
AllowedValues.Description: Output severities in eight levels, the value could be 0,1,2,3,4,5,6,7.

Enums.Description: The type of text analysis output.

Enums.Name: AnalyzeImageOutputType

AllowedValues.Name: FourSeverityLevels
AllowedValues.Description: Output severities in four levels, the value could be 0,2,4,6.

Enums.Description: The type of image analysis output.

Properties.Name: text
Properties.Description: The text needs to be analyzed. We support a maximum of 10k Unicode characters (Unicode code points) in the text of one request.

Properties.Name: categories
Properties.Description: The categories will be analyzed. If they are not assigned, a default set of analysis results for the categories will be returned.

Properties.Name: blocklistNames
Properties.Description: The names of blocklists.

Properties.Name: haltOnBlocklistHit
Properties.Description: When set to true, further analyses of harmful content will not be performed in cases where blocklists are hit. When set to false, all analyses of harmful content will be performed, whether or not blocklists are hit.

Properties.Name: outputType
Properties.Description: This refers to the type of text analysis output. If no value is assigned, the default value will be "FourSeverityLevels".

Properties.Name: blocklistsMatch
Properties.Description: The blocklist match details.

Properties.Name: blocklistName
Properties.Description: The name of the matched blocklist.

Properties.Name: blocklistItemId
Properties.Description: The ID of the matched item.

Properties.Name: blocklistItemText
Properties.Description: The content of the matched item.

Properties.Name: categoriesAnalysis
Properties.Description: Analysis result for categories.

Properties.Name: category
Properties.Description: The text analysis category.

Properties.Name: severity
Properties.Description: The value increases with the severity of the input content. The value of this field is determined by the output type specified in the request. The output type could be ‘FourSeverityLevels’ or ‘EightSeverity Levels’, and the output value can be 0, 2, 4, 6 or 0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, or 7.

Properties.Name: image
Properties.Description: The image needs to be analyzed.

Type.Name: ContentSafetyImageData
Type.Description: The image can be either base64 encoded bytes or a blob URL. You can choose only one of these options. If both are provided, the request will be refused. The maximum image size is 2048 x 2048 pixels and should not exceed 4 MB, while the minimum image size is 50 x 50 pixels.

Properties.Name: content
Properties.Description: The Base64 encoding of the image.

Properties.Name: BlobUri
Properties.Description: The blob url of the image.

Properties.Name: categories
Properties.Description: The categories will be analyzed. If they are not assigned, a default set of analysis results for the categories will be returned.

Properties.Name: outputType
Properties.Description: This refers to the type of image analysis output. If no value is assigned, the default value will be "FourSeverityLevels".

Properties.Name: categoriesAnalysis
Properties.Description: Analysis result for categories.

Properties.Name: category
Properties.Description: The image analysis category.

Properties.Name: severity
Properties.Description: The value increases with the severity of the input content. The value of this field is determined by the output type specified in the request. The output type could be ‘FourSeverityLevels’, and the output value can be 0, 2, 4, 6.

Operations.Name: analyzeText
Operations.Description: A synchronous API for the analysis of potentially harmful text content. Currently, it supports four categories: Hate, SelfHarm, Sexual, and Violence.

Parameters.Name: endpoint
Parameters.Description:
Supported Cognitive Services endpoints (protocol and hostname, for example:
https://<resource-name>.cognitiveservices.azure.com).

Parameters.Name: apiVersion
Parameters.Description: The API version to use for this operation.

Parameters.Name: options
Parameters.Description: The text analysis request.
